g.text: A single UMEMarea holding multiple mempool buffers regionsUsing MMAPor some allocation method create a single UMEMarea to help all the mempool buffers regions1.Call mp = mempool_create_empty() to allocate a mempool structure 2.Call mempool_populate(mp, addr, len) to add the mempool buffer region and initialize the buffers3.Call mempool_populate(mp) to initialize the mempool buffers or MBUFsEach socket created has its own RX/TX/CQ/FQrings/queuesThe design allows us to share a single UMEM, but limit the number of mbufs/buffers per socket without having to copy the packet data between AF_XDP sockets
